anybody got a fiction press acount if so please read does n e one have a fictionpress account if so then please read my story haze deaths redemption and the assassins creed at this link http www fictionpress com secure live preview php storyid for some strange reason they dont show up as updated stories in thee categories of stories so nobody can see them unless i ask them to for example i add a chapter to the assassins creed and i look for it expecting it to show up in the category but it doesn't can sum help a brother out and read them please i return reviews the best way i can help you out is to tell you that it is a big mistake to post anything online you ever plan on trying to publish it is an automatic rejection posting a story online automatically eliminates it from being published by practically any publisher in america read submission guidelines publishers do not want material previously posted online period the internet is a playground for plagiarists anything posted online can and will be copied if it has any merit whatsoever bad authors need not worry their work is safe but decent material is stolen every day it a publisher has to worry about tracing a work back to the original owner and proving ownership they will take a pass it just isn't worth it to them to pay lawyers for that kind of work it can be a terrible mess to untangle many sites inexperienced authors post on even have fine print giving them the rights to any and all material posted on their site by posting there you give your work away it is true that your work is your intellectual property and that you own the rights to it the second you write it however those rights are only as good as the lawyers you pay to defend them honestly it usually is not worth it to defend those rights it is too expensive to have a lawyer to defend your rights even if you could track down the person online who stole your work the answer is simple smart authors post nothing online anymore not even on their own websites i closed mine down long ago i had a bad experience when i lost a great story to a plagiarist i posted it on the site of a friend as a favor to him about months later another friend sent me an e mail saying you have to read this great story i did it was my story with someone else's name on it it was hardly worth it for me to pay an internet security specialist to find the guy and a lawyer to sue him i let the story go and closed down my site deleting everything i had posted anywhere i give this information here repeatedly others do too and yet novice writers continue to post material here and at other fiction sites it is very foolish to do it makes your work worth absolutely nothing to you as a source of any kind of income best advice find an unbiased teacher writers group or mentor and show it to them don't post online pax c Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Plagiarism Plame affair Fan fiction Public domain PHP Theory of conduct Ajax (programming) Cross site scripting Scientology versus The Internet Slashdot trolling phenomena Gmail Legal research Copyright Fair use Blog Digital rights management Journalism ethics and standards John Lott H2G2 Enterprise content management Slashdot subculture The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy Spyware Trademark Web crawler SCO-Linux controversies World Wide Web OpenDocument Canon (fiction) Diablo II: Lord of Destruction Fire Emblem: Blazing Sword Intellectual property HTTP cookie Fair Game (Scientology) Socrates Objectivist philosophy Academic publishing Chuck Palahniuk Roswell UFO incident Ethics Copyleft Thomas Paine National Kidney Foundation Singapore E-mail spam The nature of God in Western theology The Joker's Wild Social rule Windows Vista Oxford English Dictionary Computer virus Password Appeal Anne Rice HyperText Transfer Protocol MMORPG Transformation problem Scots law Property (ownership right) Wikipedia Shaggy dog story Unlawful combatant GameFAQs Quentin Tarantino Book United States Postal Se